  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nBug\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nWhen i click the destroy button, The page is expected to become blank. When i check the chrome memory, can see some Detached Element. I think memory leak.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15266646/42574151-8ac74a62-8550-11e8-8df7-9287d7a6d9db.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nNo Detached Element. \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15266646/42573991-266cf846-8550-11e8-9fe2-9a4edf4e291b.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\n\"react\": \"^16.4.1\"\r\n\"react-dom\": \"^16.4.1\"\r\n\r\nCode like: \r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport * as React from 'react'\r\nimport * as ReactDOM from 'react-dom'\r\n\r\nconst app = document.getElementById('app') as Element\r\n\r\nclass PortalTest extends React.Component {\r\n  render() {\r\n    return ReactDOM.createPortal(\r\n      <div>Test</div>,\r\n      document.body\r\n    )\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nclass PortalApp extends React.Component {\r\n  render() {\r\n    return [\r\n      <PortalTest key=\"test\" />,\r\n      <div key=\"hello\">Hello</div>,\r\n      <button key=\"button\" onClick={() => {\r\n        const bool = ReactDOM.unmountComponentAtNode(app)\r\n        console.log(bool)\r\n      }}>destroy</button>\r\n    ]\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nReactDOM.render(\r\n  <PortalApp />,\r\n  app,\r\n)\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n",
